===Mainstream===

Several Japanese goo-television shows focus on contestants who battle by answering a series of questions.  The victor of these battles then gets to decide the punishment for the loser.  Usually, these punishments resemble [[Television|Nickelodeon's Slime Time]] in that the loser is dunked or dumped in some sort of polymer or cornstarch mixture.

===Slip’n’Slide===

Of course, some [[Animal abuse|Japanese pervert]] who was a fan of Lotion play had to make a game show that involves [[Old people|very old Japanese men]] sliding over a track made of goo-covered sexy young females.  Points are given to contestants for distance and artistic or imaginative sliding.  Failure results in the slider being attacked by the girls and publically [[Ruination|humiliated]] by being stripped naked.  I do not see how losing can be bad.

